From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: MeshCore Security Audit <audit@meshcore.local>
Date: Tue, 22 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] bug22: Add hardware watchdog (WDT) for nRF52 platforms

The nRF52840 has no watchdog configured. A HardFault during flash
operations (the suspected bug22 root cause) causes an infinite loop in
the Adafruit BSP HardFault handler — the device never recovers.

This patch adds a hardware watchdog timer (WDT) that:
- Configures a timeout via NRF_WDT registers (default 10 seconds)
- Is fed (kicked) in every loop() iteration
- Automatically resets the MCU on HardFault, deadlock, or any hang
- Uses the HALT+SLEEP run behavior so the WDT keeps counting during
  debug halts and sleep (conservative safe default)
- Is configurable via CLI: set wdt <0-255>, get wdt
  - 0 = disabled, 1-255 = timeout in seconds
  - Takes effect on next reboot (WDT hardware is lock-once)
- Persisted in NodePrefs at offset 291 (1 byte)

The WDT is initialized after prefs are loaded in setup(), and fed via
NRF52Board::feedWatchdog() called from each variant's loop().

OTA update is not affected: the DFU service resets the MCU via
NVIC_SystemReset() which clears the WDT. The bootloader runs without
the watchdog until the new application starts and re-enables it.

Default value: 0 (disabled). This is safe for existing devices that
upgrade — their prefs file has 0x00 at offset 291 (never written),
so the WDT stays off until explicitly enabled via "set wdt 10".
